Merge<TKey, TValue>(params IDictionary<TKey, TValue>?[])

Merges multiple dictionaries into a single dictionary. The first non null entry will be used to merge the others into. If multiple dictionary contain the same key, the value of the last dictionary with that key will be used.

public static IDictionary<TKey, TValue>? Merge<TKey, TValue>(params IDictionary<TKey, TValue>?[] aDictionaries)

Parameters

aDictionaries IDictionary<TKey, TValue>[]

Dictionaries to merge (can be null)

Returns

IDictionary<TKey, TValue>

The first non null parameter with the values of all others merged into it. If all parameters are null, the method will return null.
